applied (codex effort xhigh -> high) before family/version fallback; original_pair=codex->claude; degraded_pair=codex->claude; remaining_headroom=82.0%\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+step-3: reason=same-provider verify fallback attempted but no same-provider verify candidate was available; original_pair=codex->claude; degraded_pair=codex->claude; remaining_headroom=82.0%\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## T-011@20260408T223256Z (2026-04-09T01:05:00+00:00)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Reason:** LOCAL_ONLY scope assumption\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Details:** This task treats `LOCAL_ONLY` as a daemon-level LLM routing guard. When enabled, all daemon agent-execution paths that would otherwise target `claude`, `codex`, or `gemini` are coerced to `ollama`, including router fallback and explicit step payloads. Non-agent operational commands (for example Telegram delivery, shell built-ins, or health probes) remain unchanged. No new dependencies are planned.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## T-012@20260408T223256Z (2026-04-09T01:30:00+00:00)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Reason:** Transport and dependency scope assumptions\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Details:** This task uses stdlib-only HTTP probing (`urllib.request`) and `subprocess` for `tailscale status --json` — no new external dependencies. The identity endpoint is probed over plain HTTP on port 8443 (matching the federation PRD convention); TLS/signing verification is deferred to a future federation identity task (FD-001/FD-005). The module lives in `promptclaw/federation/discovery.py` following the PRD architecture layout. Peers are identified by `instance_id` for merge deduplication. Offline Tailscale peers are excluded from probing.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## T-021@20260416T043834Z (2026-04-16T05:00:00+00:00)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Reason:** Candidate hardening items are out of scope\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- **Details:** The auto-generated hardening checks reference `bootstrap_identity` and `FirstBootAnnouncer`, which belong to the federation/identity subsystem. This task (self-critique and revision passes for music composition) has no relation to the startup identity flow. No new dependencies required; stdlib only.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+exec\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+/bin/zsh -lc 'cat specs/t-021@20260416t043834z-spec.md' in /Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ succeeded in 0ms:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# Spec: T-021@20260416T043834Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Problem Statement\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+CypherClaw currently generates musical scores and plays them immediately. There is\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+no pre-performance quality check: a piece with poor interval variety, weak hook\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+clarity, or excessive repetition goes straight to the speakers. The continuous\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+learner reflects *during* and *after* playback, but by then the audience has already\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+heard the weak material.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+This task adds a self-critique layer that runs *before* performance when practical.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+A generated score is converted to a fast offline preview (frequency events), analyzed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+by the ear engine, and gated against quality thresholds. If metrics fail, the system\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+requests one bounded rewrite pass with a different variation seed, then picks\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+whichever version scores better — provided it improves at least one failed metric\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+without changing the piece's identity (key, mood, tempo, family).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Technical Approach\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+1. **New module `my-claw/tools/senseweave/self_critique.py`** — sits between\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   `generative_scores.score_from_mood()` and playback. Stdlib only, no new deps.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+2. **`preview_score(score: Score) -> dict[str, float]`** — converts a Score to\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   frequency events via `score_to_frequencies()`, builds `_EarEvent` objects from\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   those frequencies, and runs `ear_engine._analyze_events()` to produce the full\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   metric dict. This is the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"offline fast preview render\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" required by AC-1.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+3. **`critique_score(score: Score, thresholds: Mapping | None) -> CritiqueReport`**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   — wraps `preview_score()` and compares each metric against configurable\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   thresholds. Returns a frozen dataclass with `passed: bool`,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   `failed_metrics: tuple[str, ...]`, and the raw metrics.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   Default thresholds (all corrective scores are bad-high, quality scores are\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   bad-low):\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   - `underdeveloped_score` > 0.7 → fail\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   - `static_score` > 0.7 → fail\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   - `development_score` < 0.25 → fail\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   - `hook_clarity` < 0.2 → fail\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+4. **`revise_score(mood, *, thresholds, max_passes=1, **mood_kwargs) -> RevisionResult`**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   — generates an initial score via `score_from_mood()`, critiques it. If it\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   passes, returns immediately. If it fails, regenerates with `variation_seed + 1`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   (one bounded rewrite pass, AC-2). Compares original and revised metrics, picks\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   the version where at least one failed metric improved. Verifies identity\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   preservation (same key, mood string, tempo_bpm).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+5. **Dataclasses:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   - `CritiqueReport(metrics, passed, failed_metrics)`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   - `RevisionResult(original_score, original_metrics, revised_score,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+     revised_metrics, improved_metrics, identity_preserved, revision_used)`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Edge Cases\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Score with very few notes (sleeping mode, 4 notes) — thresholds may naturally\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  fail for short pieces. `critique_score` applies to any score; callers decide\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  whether to gate sleeping pieces.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- All metrics pass on first try — `revise_score` returns the original with\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  `revision_used=False`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Revision is worse on all failed metrics — system keeps the original, returns\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  `revision_used=False` and `improved_metrics=()`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `variation_seed` is None — rewrite pass uses seed 1 for the original and seed 2\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  for the revision.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Custom thresholds override defaults — caller can tighten or loosen any metric.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Assumptions\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- The candidate hardening items referencing `bootstrap_identity` and\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  `FirstBootAnnouncer` are federation-scoped and do not apply to this music\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  composition task. Documented in ESCALATIONS.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- No new external dependencies required (stdlib only).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Acceptance Criteria\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+1. Offline preview render can be analyzed before playback for new pieces.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_self_critique.py::TestPreviewScore -q`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+2. Composition gate can request one bounded rewrite pass for failed metrics.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_self_critique.py::TestReviseScore::test_revision_requested_for_failed_metrics -q`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+3. Tests verify rewrite improves at least one target metric without changing piece\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   identity.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_self_critique.py::TestReviseScore::test_revision_improves_at_least_one_metric -q`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+4. Identity preservation: revised score keeps key, mood, and tempo unchanged.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_self_critique.py::TestReviseScore::test_identity_preserved_after_revision -q`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+5. When original passes, no revision is attempted.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_self_critique.py::TestReviseScore::test_no_revision_when_passing -q`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+6. When revision is worse on all failed metrics, original is kept.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_self_critique.py::TestReviseScore::test_keeps_original_when_revision_worse -q`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+7. Max one rewrite pass is enforced (bounded).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+   VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_self_critique.py::TestReviseScore::test_max_one_rewrite_pass -q`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+exec\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+/bin/zsh -lc 'git diff HEAD~3' in /Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+exec\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+/bin/zsh -lc 'git diff HEAD~3 --stat' in /Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ succeeded in 1756ms:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ CHANGELOG.md                                       |   104 +\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ docs/20260402-cypherclaw-embodiment-prd.md         |   308 +\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ ...0260402-cypherclaw-embodiment-research-brief.md |   158 +\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ docs/architecture.md                               |    61 +-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ docs/codex-audio-investigation-brief.md            |   153 +\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ docs/command-reference.md                          |   140 +-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ docs/contact-mic-calibration-protocol.md           |   301 +\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ docs/cypherclaw-emsd-roadmap.md                    |   423 +\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md            |   504 +\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ docs/cypherclaw-presence-cadence-spec.md           |   986 +\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ docs/cypherclaw-score-tree-composition-spec.md     |   618 +\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ docs/cypherclaw-tracker-framework.md   